ert E. |authorlink=Robert E. Quirk |year=1993 |publisher=W.W. Norton & Company |location=New York and London |isbn=978-0393034851 |ref=harv |url=https://archive.org/details/fidelcastro00robe }}\n: {{Cite book|last=Sampson |first=Anthony |authorlink=Anthony Sampson |title=[[Mandela: The Authorised Biography]] |publisher=HarperCollins |location= |year=1999 |isbn= 978-0006388456 |ref=Sam99}}\n: {{cite book |title=Fidel Castro: A Biography |last=Skierka |first=Volka |year=2006 |publisher=Polity |location=Cambridge |isbn=978-0745640815 |ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book |title=Red Heat: Conspiracy, Murder, and the Cold War in the Caribbean |last=Von Tunzelmann |first=Alex |year=2011 |publisher=Henry Holt and Company |location=New York City |isbn=978-0805090673 |ref=harv |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/redheatconspirac0000vont }}\n: {{cite book |title=Changing Venezuela by Taking Power: The History and Policies of the Ch\u00e1vez Government |last=Wilpert |first=Gregory |year=2007 |publisher=Verso |location=London and New York |isbn=978-1844675524 |ref=harv |url=https://archive.org/details/changingvenezuel00wilp }}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{Fidel Castro}}\n\n[[Category:Fidel Castro]]\n[[Category:1950s in Cuba]]\n[[Category:1960s in Cuba]]\n[[Category:1970s in Cuba]]\n[[Category:1980s in Cuba]]\n[[Category:1990s in Cuba]]\n[[Category:2000s in Cuba]]\n[[Category:20th-century Cuban politicians]]<!--as Premiership-->\n[[Category:Presidencies|Castro, Fidel]]\n", "name_user": "2600:1700:1d77:1130:d039:cc41:1b24:e41c", "label": "vandal", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cuba_under_Fidel_Castro"}
{"title_page": "Baire function", "text_new": "In [[mathematics]], '''Baire functions''' are [[function (mathematics)|function]]s obtained from [[continuous functions]] by transfinite iteration of the operation of forming pointwise limits of sequences of functions. They were introduced by [[Ren\u00e9-Louis Baire]] in 1899. A [[Baire set]] is a set whose [[indicator function|characteristic function]] is a Baire function. (There are other, almost equivalent, but inequivalent definitions of Baire sets.)\n\n==Classification of Baire functions==\nBaire functions of class \u03b1, for any countable [[ordinal number]] \u03b1, form a [[vector space]] of [[Real number|real]]-valued functions defined on a [[topological space]], as follows.\n\n*The Baire class 0 functions are the [[Continuous function (topology)|continuous function]]s.\n*The Baire class 1 functions are those functions which are the [[Pointwise convergence|pointwise limit]] of a [[sequence]] of Baire class 0 functions.\n*In general, the Baire class \u03b1 functions are all functions which are the pointwise limit of a sequence of functions of Baire class less than \u03b1.\n\nSome authors define the classes slightly differently, by removing all functions of class less than \u03b1 from the functions of class \u03b1. This means that each Baire function has a well defined class, but the functions of given class no longer form a vector space.\n\n[[Henri Lebesgue]] proved that (for functions on the [[unit interval]]) each Baire class of a countable ordinal number contains functions not in any smaller class, and that there exist functions which are not in any Baire class.\n\n==Baire class 1==\nExamples:\n*The [[derivative]] of any [[differentiable function]] is of class 1. An example of a differentiable function whose derivative is not continuous (at ''x''&thinsp;=&thinsp;0) is the function equal to <math>x^2 \\sin(1/x)</math> when ''x''&thinsp;\u2260&thinsp;0, and 0 when ''x''&thinsp;=&thinsp;0. An infinite sum of similar functions (scaled and displaced by [[rational number]]s) can even give a differentiable function whose derivative is discontinuous on a dense set. However, it necessarily has points of continuity, which follows easily from The Baire Characterisation Theorem (below; take ''K''&thinsp;=&thinsp;''X''&thinsp;=&thinsp;'''R''').\n*The characteristic function of the set of [[integer]]s, which equals 1 if ''x'' is an integer and 0 otherwise. (An infinite number of large discontinuities.)\n*[[Thomae's function]], which is 0 for [[Irrational number|irrational]] ''x'' and 1/''q'' for a rational number ''p''/''q'' (in reduced form). (A dense set of discontinuities, namely the set of rational numbers.)\n*The characteristic function of the [[Cantor set]], which equals 1 if ''x'' is in the Cantor set and 0 otherwise. This function is 0 for an uncountable set of ''x'' values, and 1 for an uncountable set. It is discontinuous wherever it equals 1 and continuous wherever it equals 0. It is approximated by the continuous functions <math>g_n(x) = \\max(0,{1-nd(x,C)})</math>, where <math>d(x,C)</math> is the distance of x from the nearest point in the Cantor set.\n\nThe Baire Characterisation Theorem states that a real valued function ''f'' defined on a [[Banach space]] ''X'' is a Baire-1 function if and only if for every [[Empty set|non-empty]] [[Metric_space#Open_and_closed_sets,_topology_and_convergence|closed]] subset ''K'' of ''X'', the [[Restriction (mathematics)|restriction]] of ''f'' to ''K'' has a point of continuity relative to the [[Topological space|topology]] of ''K''.\n\nBy another theorem of Baire, for every Baire-1 function the points of continuity are a [[comeager]] [[G\u03b4 set|''G''<sub>\u03b4</sub> set]] {{harv|Kechris|1995|loc=Theorem (24.14)}}.\n\n==Baire class 2==\nExamples:\n*An example of a Baire class 2 function on the interval [0,1] that is not of class 1 is the characteristic function of the rational numbers, <math>\\chi_\\mathbb{Q}</math>, also known as the [[Dirichlet function]]. It is discontinuous everywhere. This can be seen by noting that for any finite collection of rationals, the characteristic function for this set is Baire 1: namely the function <math>g_n(x) = \\max(0,{1-nd(x,K)})</math> converges identically to the characteristic function of <math>K</math>, where <math>K</math> is the finite collection of rationals. Since the rationals are countable, we can look at the pointwise limit of these things over <math>K_n = \\{r_1,r_2,\\dots,r_n\\}</math>, where <math>r_n</math> is an enumeration of the rationals. It is not Baire-1 by the theorem mentioned above: the set of discontinuities is the entire interval (certainly, the set of points of continuity is not comeager).\n\n==Baire class 3==\nExamples:\n{{Expand section|date=November 2013}}\n\n==See also==\n\n*[[Baire set]]\n*[[Nowhere continuous function]]\n\n==References==\n*{{cite thesis|type=Ph.D.|first=Ren\u00e9-Louis|last=Baire|title=Sur les fonctions de variables r\u00e9elles|publisher= \u00c9cole Normale Sup\u00e9rieure |year=1899|url=https://archive.org/details/surlesfonctions00bairgoog}}\n*{{citation|first=Ren\u00e9-Louis|last=Baire|title=Le\u00e7ons sur les fonctions discontinues, profess\u00e9es au coll\u00e8ge de France|publisher= Gauthier-Villars |year=1905}}.\n*{{citation|first=Alexander S.|last=Kechris|author-link=Alexander S. Kechris|title=Classical Descriptive Set Theory|publisher=Springer-Verlag|year=1995}}.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://eom.springer.de/b/b015030.htm Springer Encyclopaedia of Mathematics article on Baire classes]\n\n[[Category:General topology]]\n[[Category:Real analysis]]\n[[Category:Types of functions]]\n", "text_old": "In [[mathematics]], '''Baire functions''' are [[function (mathematics)|function]]s obtained from [[continuous functions]] by transfinite iteration of the operation of forming pointwise limits of sequences of functions. They were introduced by [[Ren\u00e9-Louis Baire]] in 1899. A [[Baire set]] is a set whose [[indicator function|characteristic function]] is a Baire function. (There are other, almost equivalent, but inequivalent definitions of Baire sets.)\n\n==Classification of Baire functions==\nBaire functions of class \u03b1, for any countable [[ordinal number]] \u03b1, form a vector space of real-valued functions defined on a [[topological space]], as follows.\n\n*The Baire class 0 functions are the [[continuous function]]s.\n*The Baire class 1 functions are those functions which are the [[pointwise convergence|pointwise limit]] of a [[sequence]] of Baire class 0 functions.\n*In general, the Baire class \u03b1 functions are all functions which are the pointwise limit of a sequence of functions of Baire class less than \u03b1.\n\nSome authors define the classes slightly differently, by removing all functions of class less than \u03b1 from the functions of class \u03b1. This means that each Baire function has a well defined class, but the functions of given class no longer form a vector space.\n\n[[Henri Lebesgue]] proved that (for functions on the unit interval) each Baire class of a countable ordinal number contains functions not in any smaller class, and that there exist functions which are not in any Baire class.\n\n==Baire class 1==\nExamples:\n*The [[derivative]] of any [[differentiable function]] is of class 1. An example of a differentiable function whose derivative is not continuous (at ''x''=0) is the function equal to <math>x^2\\sin(1/x)</math> when ''x''\u22600, and 0 when ''x''=0. An infinite sum of similar functions (scaled and displaced by rational numbers) can even give a differentiable function whose derivative is discontinuous on a dense set. However, it necessarily has points of continuity, which follows easily from The Baire Characterisation Theorem (below; take ''K''=''X''='''R''').\n*The characteristic function of the set of integers, which equals 1 if ''x'' is an integer and 0 otherwise. (An infinite number of large discontinuities.)\n*[[Thomae's function]], which is 0 for irrational ''x'' and 1/''q'' for a rational number ''p''/''q'' (in reduced form). (A dense set of discontinuities, namely the set of rational numbers.)\n*The characteristic function of the [[Cantor set]], which equals 1 if ''x'' is in the Cantor set and 0 otherwise. This function is 0 for an uncountable set of ''x'' values, and 1 for an uncountable set. It is discontinuous wherever it equals 1 and continuous wherever it equals 0. It is approximated by the continuous functions <math>g_n(x)=\\max(0,{1-nd(x,C)})</math>, where <math>d(x,C)</math> is the distance of x from the nearest point in the Cantor set.\n\nThe Baire Characterisation Theorem states that a real valued function f defined on a [[Banach space]] X is a Baire-1 function if and only if for every non-empty closed subset K of X, the restriction of f to K has a point of continuity relative to the topology of K.\n\nBy another theorem of Baire, for every Baire-1 function the points of continuity are a [[comeager]] [[G\u03b4 set|''G''<sub>\u03b4</sub> set]] {{harv|Kechris|1995|loc=Theorem (24.14)}}.\n\n==Baire class 2==\nExamples:\n*An example of a Baire class two function on the interval [0,1] that is not of class 1 is the characteristic function of the rational numbers, <math>\\chi_\\mathbb{Q}</math>, also known as the [[Dirichlet function]]. It is discontinuous everywhere. This can be seen by noting that for any finite collection of rationals, the indicator function for this set is Baire 1: namely the function <math>g_n(x) = \\max(0,{1-nd(x,K)})</math> converges identically to the indicator function of <math>K</math>, where <math>K</math> is the finite collection of rationals. Since the rationals are countable, we can look at the pointwise limit of these things over <math>K_n = \\{r_1,r_2,\\dots,r_n\\}</math>, where <math>r_n</math> is an enumeration of the rationals. It is not Baire-1 by the theorem mentioned above: the set of discontinuities is the entire interval (certainly, the set of points of continuity is not comeager).\n\n==Baire class 3==\nExamples:\n{{Expand section|date=November 2013}}\n\n==See also==\n\n*[[Baire set]]\n*[[Nowhere continuous function]]\n\n==References==\n*{{cite thesis|type=Ph.D.|first=Ren\u00e9-Louis|last=Baire|title=Sur les fonctions de variables r\u00e9elles|publisher= \u00c9cole Normale Sup\u00e9rieure |year=1899|url=https://archive.org/details/surlesfonctions00bairgoog}}\n*{{citation|first=Ren\u00e9-Louis|last=Baire|title=Le\u00e7ons sur les fonctions discontinues, profess\u00e9es au coll\u00e8ge de France|publisher= Gauthier-Villars |year=1905}}.\n*{{citation|first=Alexander S.|last=Kechris|author-link=Alexander S. Kechris|title=Classical Descriptive Set Theory|publisher=Springer-Verlag|year=1995}}.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://eom.springer.de/b/b015030.htm Springer Encyclopaedia of Mathematics article on Baire classes]\n\n[[Category:General topology]]\n[[Category:Real analysis]]\n[[Category:Types of functions]]\n", "name_user": "Joel Brennan", "label": "safe", "comment": "added wikilinks", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baire_function"}
{"title_page": "True Corporation", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}golemher\n\n'''True Corporation Public Company Limited''' (TRUE) is a communications conglomerate in [[Thailand]]. True controls Thailand's largest cable TV provider, [[TrueVisions]],<ref>https://techsauce.co/pr-news/true-digital-park-unveiled-first-set-of-partners/</ref> Thailand's largest internet service provider '''True Internet'''{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} and one of Thailand's largest mobile operators, '''TrueMove H''', which is second only to [[Advanced Info Service|AIS]] having surpassed [[Dtac]] in January 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.developingtelecoms.com/business/operator-news/7040-true-takes-second-place-in-thai-market-as-dtac-profits-slump.html|title=True takes second place in Thai market as Dtac profits slump|last=Barton|first=James|website=Developing Telecoms|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref> As of August 2014, True, along with True Telecommunications Growth Infrastructure Fund, had a combined market capitalization of US$10 billion.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} TrueMove is also a partner of [[Vodafone Group]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Vodafone and Conexus Mobile Alliance Form Strategic Partnership |url=https://www.vodafone.com/content/index/media/vodafone-group-releases/2011/conexus_partnership.html |website=www.vodafone.com |accessdate=21 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nTrue is a subsidiary of [[Charoen Pokphand Group]], which holds 50.21 percent of True's shares as of March 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://investor.truecorp.co.th/shareholders.html|title=Investor Relations|last=Shareinvestor|website=True|access-date=2017-06-08}}</ref> It operates fixed-line (as a concessionaire of TOT), [[wireless]], [[cable TV]], [[IPTV]] and [[broadband]] services.\n\n==History==\nTrue Corporation was established on 13 November 1990 as '''TelecomAsia'''.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com/thailand/bangkok-post/20150330/282574491577094|title=PressReader.com - Connecting People Through News|website=www.pressreader.com|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref> The company had partnership with [[Verizon]].<ref name=\":0\" /> The company was listed on the [[Stock Exchange of Thailand]] on {{Start date|1993|12|22}}.<ref name=\"SETCompanyProfile\">{{cite web|title=TRUE Company Profile|url=http://www.set.or.th/set/companyprofile.do?Bahtsymbol=TRUE|website=Stock Exchange of Thailand|accessdate=3 July 2010}}</ref> In 2001, TelecomAsia set up a mobile phone subsidiary with [[Orange S.A.|Orange SA]]. Orange sold off its stake in 2003 but the Orange brand was used until 2006.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0FGI/is_4_15/ai_n6040967 | work=Telecom Asia | title=TA Orange's strategic partner Orange SA sells off 39% of its 49% stake in the Thai mobile operator to TelecomAsia for a nominal one Baht | date=2004-04-01}}</ref>\n\nIn an effort to converge TelecomAsia's telecommunication business into a single brand, the company renamed itself to True Corporation in 2004,<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.th/books?id=dPgGGhvgfikC&pg=PA336&lpg=PA336&dq=2004+TRUe+corporation+telecomasia&source=bl&ots=cTEdP5f0Bj&sig=Byje3UIm7DLGZGAizorADXs7ldE&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjhiPqepYvZAhWEsY8KHT2-BhAQ6AEIVTAJ#v=onepage&q=2004%20TRUe%20corporation%20telecomasia&f=false|title=Southeast Asia's Chinese Businesses in an Era of Globalization: Coping with the Rise of China|last=Suryadinata|first=Leo|date=2006|publisher=Institute of Southeast Asian Studies|isbn=9789812304018|language=en}}</ref> and streamlined its operations with subsidiaries Asia Infonet (renamed True Internet{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}}) and Orange (renamed True Move in 2006<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegeography.com/products/commsupdate/articles/2006/02/08/orange-reaches-use-by-date-true-corps-mobile-unit-renamed-true-move/|title=Orange reaches use-by date: True Corp's mobile unit renamed True Move|website=TeleGeography|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref>).\n\nIn 2005, True took a higher stake in [[United Broadcasting Corporation|UBC]], Thailand's largest [[cable television]] provider that time{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}}, and renamed the company to UBC-True.<ref>Amnatcharoenrit, Bamrung and Tortermvasana, Komsan (8 November 2005). [http://www.asiamedia.ucla.edu/article.asp?parentid=33025 \"True Corp set to take over UBC\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080311233416/http://www.asiamedia.ucla.edu/article.asp?parentid=33025 |date=2008-03-11}}, ''Bangkok Post'' (retrieved 18 July 2006 until 18 August 2015 via AsiaMedia.com).</ref> On 24 January 2007 UBC-True was renamed [[TrueVisions]].{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\nOn 8 May 2013, TrueMove H became Thailand's first mobile operator to provide 4G LTE commercial service on the 2100&nbsp;MHz bandwidth.<ref name=\"thaipr\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thaipr.net/communication/476291|title=True Move H \u2013 The First To Offer 4G LTE Service On 2100 MHz In Thailand While Reinforcing Its Leadership As The Largest 3G Operator,|work=thaipr.net}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 September 2014, it was announced that [[China Mobile]] agreed to purchase 18 percent of its shares for US$881 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=China Mobile to buy $881mln stake in Thai billionaire's True Corp|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/06/09/us-true-corporation-chinamobile-idUSKBN0EK0QA20140609|date=June 9, 2014|author=Jittapong, Khettiya|accessdate=11 June 2014| agency=[[Reuters]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=China Mobile to buy into True |url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/business/news/414439/china-mobile-to-buy-into-true|date=June 10, 2014|author1=Phoosuphanusorn, Srisamorn  |author2=Leesa-nguansuk, Suchit |lastauthoramp=yes |accessdate=June 11, 2014|work=Bangkok Post}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 November 2014, Truemove H announced that it allocated 10 billion baht to expand its 4G LTE network in Thailand to cover 80 percent of the country's population.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mobileasia.net/?p=10252|title=True announced high-speed Internet in Bangkok with all-fiber network in 2 years|work=Mobileasia}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2015 [[Suphachai Chearavanont]], True's President and CEO, was presented with the \"2015 [[Frost & Sullivan]] Asia Pacific Telecom CEO of the Year\" award in Singapore for his leadership and achievements in developing the telecommunications industry in the Asia Pacific region.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} In the same month, Chearavanont was elected president of The Telecommunications Association of Thailand.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n\n==Subsidiaries==\nTrue Corporation includes the following subsidiaries:<ref>{{cite web|title=Annual Report 2014|url=http://true.listedcompany.com/misc/AR/ar2014-en.html}}</ref>\n* [[TrueMove H|TrueMobile]] (Mobile telecommunication)\n** True Move Co., Ltd.\n** Real Move Co., Ltd.\n** True Move H Universal Communication Co., Ltd.\n** BFKT (Thailand) Limited\n* TrueOnline (Broadband/fixed line business)\n** Asia Infonet Co., Ltd.\n** Asia Wireless Communication Co., Ltd.\n** KSC Commercial Internet Co., Ltd.\n** MKSC World Dot Com Co., Ltd.\n** True International Communication Co., Ltd.\n** True International Gateway Co., Ltd.\n** True Internet Co., Ltd.\n** True Public Communication Co., Ltd.\n** True Universal Convergence Co., Ltd.\n* [[TrueVisions]] (Pay TV business)\n** BEC-TERO True Visions Co., Ltd.\n** Click TV Co., Ltd.\n** Satellite Service Co., Ltd.\n** Thai News Network (TNN) Co., Ltd.\n** True4U Station Co., Ltd.\n** [[TrueVisions|True Visions Plc.]]\n** True Visions Cable Plc.\n** True Visions Group Co., Ltd.\n** True Vistas Co., Ltd.\n* Content, lifestyle and other businesses:\n** AP&J Production Co., Ltd.\n** Cineplex Co., Ltd.\n** True CJ Creations (joint venture with South Korea's [[CJ ENM]])\n** Panther Entertainment Co., Ltd.\n** SM True (joint venture with South Korea's [[S.M. Entertainment]])<ref>{{cite web|title=True Group, in Collaboration with S.M. Entertainment from South Korea, Establishes a Joint-Venture \"SM True Co., Ltd.\"To Bring A New Era of Entertainment to Thailand|url=http://www2.truecorp.co.th/en/pc_press_detail.aspx?id=1443|work=True Corporation|accessdate=16 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=S.M. Entertainment establishes joint venture company with Thailand\u2019s True Visions Group, \u2018SM True\u2019|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/08/sm-entertainment-establishes-joint-venture-company-with-thailands-true-visions-group-sm-true|work=[[allkpop]]|accessdate=16 August 2011}}</ref>\n** True Digital Media Co., Ltd.\n** True Distribution & Sales Co., Ltd.\n** True IContent Co., Ltd.\n** True Information Technology Co., Ltd.\n** True Life Plus Co., Ltd.\n** [[True Money]]\n** True Multimedia Co., Ltd.\n** True Music Co., Ltd.\n** True Music Radio Co., Ltd.\n** True Touch Co., Ltd.\n** True United Football Club Co., Ltd.\n** Transformation Films Co., Ltd.\n** True GS Co., Ltd.\n** Thai Smart Card Co., Ltd.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www3.truecorp.co.th/new/?ln=en True Corporation]\n{{Charoen Pokphand}}\n{{Major mobile device companies}}\n{{Major telecommunications companies}}\n{{FAT sponsors}}\n\n[[Category:Members of the Conexus Mobile Alliance]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1990]]\n[[Category:Telecommunications companies of Thailand]]\n[[Category:Mobile phone companies of Thailand]]\n[[Category:Mobile phone manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Charoen Pokphand Group]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Stock Exchange of Thailand]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Bangkok]]\n[[Category:1990 establishments in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Thai brands]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name             = True Corporation\n| logo             = True Corporation (Thailand).svg\n| caption          =\n| type             = [[Public limited company|Public]]\n| traded_as        = {{SET|TRUE}}\n| genre            =\n| fate  